<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM3.4.8">
<l>cinturap poṭikkoṇṭu ceṉṉi yappit</l>
<l rend="indent">tirunāma miṭṭaṅkō rilaiyan taṉṉā</l>
<l>lantara miṉṟittaṉ ṉeṟipaṅ kiyai</l>
<l rend="indent">yaḻakiya nēttirat tāla ṇin</l>
<l>tintiraṉ pōlvaru māyap piḷḷai</l>
<l rend="indent">yetirniṉṟaṅ kiṉavaḷai yiḻavē leṉṉa</l>
<l>cantiyil niṉṟukaṇ ṭīrnaṅ kaitaṉ</l>
<l rend="indent">tukiloṭu carivaḷai kaḻalkiṉ ṟatē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Standing there face-to-face with the cowherd boy</l>
<l rend="indent">who comes like Indra,</l>
<l>having taken saffron powder [and] applied [it] to [his] head,</l>
<l rend="indent">[he] placed the tiru nāmam there by means of a single leaf,</l>
<l>[and] adorned his curly hair</l>
<l rend="indent">with beautiful peacock feathers without [any] gaps,</l>
<l>while I say ‘Don’t lose [your] collection of bangles!’</l>
<l>Ladies! You saw [her] standing at the crossroads,</l>
<l rend="indent">her bangles, along with her sari become loose and slip off!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
